The paper discusses the study of arguments as abstract entities and their interaction, which is a topic within Artificial Intelligence and Reasoning (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of acceptance problems, which is a topic within computational complexity theory (cs.CR). The use of rankings and audiences in value-based argumentation suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the identification of nontrivial classes of value-based argumentation systems suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
